<p style=3D"margin-bottom:4pt; margin-top:8pt;"><b>About:</b>
<br>This tool performs conversion between the most common data transfer rat=
e units used for measurements of network speed=20
and bandwidth, file transfer rate, system and storage bandwidth, backup/rec=
overy throughput, etc.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:4pt; margin-top:4pt;">
Enter the initial data transfer rate value you'd like to convert in the Fro=
m filed, select the initial and the target measurement units,=20
and then click the Convert button.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:4pt; margin-top:4pt;">
For your convenience this tool will also convert the entered value into som=
e often used units, including GB/s, MB/s, Gbps, Mbps,
GiB/s, MiB/s.</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:8pt;"><b>Possible abbreviations f=
or bit-rate units:</b></p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:4pt; margin-top:0pt;">
&nbsp;kilobit / second - <b>kbit/s</b>, <b>kb/s</b>, or <b>kbps</b>;=20
<br>&nbsp;megabit / second - <b>Mbit/s</b>, <b>Mb/s</b>, or <b>Mbps</b>;=20
<br>&nbsp;gigabit / second - <b>Gbit/s</b>, <b>Gb/s</b>, or <b>Gbps</b>;
<br>&nbsp;terabit / second - <b>Tbit/s</b>, <b>Tb/s</b>, or <b>Tbps</b>;
</p>
<p style=3D"margin-bottom:4pt; margin-top:8pt;">
<b>Tebibyte (TiB)</b>, <b>gibibyte (GiB)</b>, <b>mebibyte (MiB)</b>, <b>kib=
ibyte (KiB)</b> are standard units used in the=20
field of data processing and data transmission. Tebibyte, gibibyte, mebibyt=
e, kibibyte are defined as powers of 2.=20
<br>Tebibyte, gibibyte, mebibyte, kibibyte are closely related to <b>teraby=
te (TB)</b>, <b>gigabyte (GB)</b>, <b>megabyte (MB)</b>,=20
and <b>kilobyte (KB</b>) respectively, which are defined as powers of 10 in=
 accordance with the International System of Units (SI).</p>
